ArcticDownloader 0.1.7 update log

Purpose:
- Track code changes made for the Windows workspace during the 0.1.7 update.

Format:
- Date
- Change summary
- Files changed
- Notes

Entries:
- 2026-03-14
  - Added Windows Intel GPU detection and a new PyTorch XPU Nightly install profile for ComfyUI installs.
  - Files changed:
    - src-tauri/src/main.rs
    - src-tauri/dist/main.js
    - version0.1.7_updates
  - Notes:
    - Intel GPU systems now auto-select the XPU profile in the installer when NVIDIA is not detected first.
    - Added fake Intel mode with `--fakeintel` for UI and profile testing.
    - XPU installs use the Windows PyTorch nightly XPU index and apply Intel launch environment variables at runtime.
- 2026-03-14
  - Ported the new Linux 0.1.7 startup flags to the Windows app.
  - Files changed:
    - src/config.rs
    - src-tauri/src/main.rs
    - src-tauri/dist/index.html
    - src-tauri/dist/main.js
    - version0.1.7_updates
  - Notes:
    - Added `--lowvram`, `--bf16-unet`, `--async-offload`, and `--disable-smart-memory` to the Windows `Flags` section.
    - These launch-only flags are now saved in app settings and used when starting ComfyUI.
    - Launch-only flag toggles now work from both `Install New` and `Manage Existing`.
- 2026-03-14
  - Added a short release-note style changelog for Windows 0.1.7.
  - Files changed:
    - CHANGELOG_0.1.7.md
    - version0.1.7_updates
  - Notes:
    - Summarizes the Windows Intel XPU work and the startup flags update without dumping internal implementation details.
